 -- Peter Zaickin <peter.zaickin@nexenta.com>  Tue, 05 Jul 2011 16:00:30 +0300

libfile-remove-perl (1.42-3) unstable; urgency=low

  * Add myself to Uploaders. 
  * Add patch bumping required Perl minimum version in META.yml. Some tests for
    libfile-remove-perl require 5.006, and the tests fail with newer
    libperl-minimumversion-perl (>= 1.22). Thanks to Lucas Nussbaum reporting
    the FTBFS (Closes: #560615).
  * Add quilt patch system for managing patches, update debian/rules with the
    --with quilt option passed to dh. Add README.source documenting use of
    quilt patch system.
  * debian/control:
    - Add quilt (>= 0.46-7) to Build-Depends.
    - Bump versioned Build-Depends on debhelper to (>= 7.0.8).
    - Replace versioned Build-Depends-Indep on perl with unversioned one since 
      5.8.8-7 is in oldstable.
    - Add alternative Build-Depends-Indep on perl (>= 5.10.1) |
      libpod-simple-perl (>= 3.07).
    - Bump Standards-Version to 3.8.3.
  * debian/copyright: Update to the current revision of the DEP5 machine
    readable format-specification proposal. 

 -- Salvatore Bonaccorso <salvatore.bonaccorso@gmail.com>  Sun, 13 Dec 2009 10:44:33 +0100

